                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 1, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 2—1 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Procedure outlined in my telegram No. 42, May 30, 3 p.m. has been carried
                    out. Foreign Minister offered to send a note today, after <pb facs="0630"
                        n="622" xml:id="pg_622"/> confirming figures of 34 percent mentioned in our
                    note, agreeing thereto, but owing to illness of Ortiz he says that he cannot do
                    so until tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
